.TP
\f[B]XMLHttpRequest.overrideMimeType()\f[R]
Overrides the MIME type returned by the server.
.TP
\f[B]XMLHttpRequest.send()\f[R]
Sends the request.
If the request is asynchronous (which is the default), this method
returns as soon as the request is sent.
.TP
\f[B]XMLHttpRequest.setAttributionReporting()\f[R] \f[I](secure context)\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
Indicates that you want the request\(cqs response to be able to register
an attribution source or trigger event.
.TP
\f[B]XMLHttpRequest.setRequestHeader()\f[R]
Sets the value of an HTTP request header.
You must call \f[CR]setRequestHeader()\f[R] after \f[CR]open()\f[R], but
before \f[CR]send()\f[R].
.SH EVENTS
.TP
\f[B]abort\f[R]
Fired when a request has been aborted, for example because the program
called \f[CR]XMLHttpRequest.abort()\f[R].
Also available via the \f[CR]onabort\f[R] event handler property.
.TP
\f[B]error\f[R]
Fired when the request encountered an error.
Also available via the \f[CR]onerror\f[R] event handler property.
.TP
\f[B]load\f[R]
Fired when an \f[CR]XMLHttpRequest\f[R] transaction completes
successfully.
Also available via the \f[CR]onload\f[R] event handler property.
.TP
\f[B]loadend\f[R]
Fired when a request has completed, whether successfully (after
\f[CR]load\f[R]) or unsuccessfully (after \f[CR]abort\f[R] or
\f[CR]error\f[R]).
Also available via the \f[CR]onloadend\f[R] event handler property.
.TP
\f[B]loadstart\f[R]
Fired when a request has started to load data.
Also available via the \f[CR]onloadstart\f[R] event handler property.
.TP
\f[B]progress\f[R]
Fired periodically when a request receives more data.
Also available via the \f[CR]onprogress\f[R] event handler property.
.TP
\f[B]readystatechange\f[R]
Fired whenever the \f[CR]readyState\f[R] property changes.
Also available via the \f[CR]onreadystatechange\f[R] event handler
property.
.TP
\f[B]timeout\f[R]
Fired when progress is terminated due to preset time expiring.
Also available via the \f[CR]ontimeout\f[R] event handler property.
